Job Title: Power BI Engineer | Mount Cotton | On Site
Category: Help Desk & IT Support (Information & Communication Technology)
Ad Text:
Robert Half has partnered with a leading Australian organisation within the food industry / supply chain sector seeking an experienced Data Engineer to support the design, development, and optimisation of enterprise data solutions powering operational and commercial decision-making.

Reporting into senior technology leadership, this role is responsible for building and maintaining robust data pipelines, backend services, and reporting platforms that enable scalable, secure, and high-performing analytics solutions. While a key component of the role involves developing Power BI dashboards and reporting outputs, the backend data architecture and transformation layer is built in C#, requiring strong hands-on development capability in that language.

You will work closely with business stakeholders, application teams, and global IT functions to ensure data solutions are reliable, governed, and aligned to broader enterprise standards.

Key Responsibilities

Design, develop, and maintain scalable data pipelines and backend services using C# and .NET technologies
Build, optimise, and manage data models to support reporting, analytics, and operational dashboards
Develop and maintain Power BI dashboards and reporting solutions aligned to business requirements
Collaborate with business stakeholders to translate reporting and analytical needs into technical data solutions
Ensure data quality, integrity, and performance across systems and integrations
Develop APIs and integration services to enable seamless data exchange across enterprise applications
Implement best practices across data governance, security, and compliance standards
Optimise query performance and manage structured and semi-structured data across SQL and related platforms
Monitor and troubleshoot data workflows, resolving performance bottlenecks and technical issues
Contribute to architectural decisions relating to data platforms, cloud services, and reporting frameworks
Document data flows, models, and technical designs to ensure maintainability and knowledge sharing
Support continuous improvement initiatives across analytics capability, automation, and reporting maturity

About You

Proven experience in a Data Engineer or backend data-focused development role
Strong hands-on experience with C# and .NET (Core / Framework) for backend data processing and services
Demonstrated experience building and maintaining Power BI dashboards and data models
Solid SQL skills with experience in data modelling, ETL processes, and performance optimisation
Experience designing APIs or integration layers supporting data exchange
Strong understanding of data governance, security, and best practice data management principles
Experience working in enterprise or complex operational environments
Ability to communicate effectively with both technical and non-technical stakeholders
Highly analytical, detail-oriented, and solutions focused
Experience within primary industries, manufacturing, supply chain, or asset-intensive environments will be highly regarded
Exposure to cloud platforms (Azure preferred) is advantageous

Salary/Benefits:
$130,000 - $165,000 + Super

Our client is currently seeking an AI Governance Advisor to complete FAIRA assessments for AI enabled applications and tools in use across their organisation.

In this role you will also support the establishment and ongoing execution of an AI Governance Committee, establish scalable monitoring and reporting related to AI governance requirements and build a toolkit for business users across the organisation to use in the application of the governance framework for their AI initiatives.

As the AI Governance Advisor, you will:

Coordinate, author, and quality assure FAIRA assessments on applications and tools in use across the organisation - integrating with privacy, security and ethics subject matter experts, and liaise with solution and/or platform owners for approvals.
Support work to engage a partner to design and implement an enterprise-wide AI governance framework (including relevant policies and standards) to ensure compliance with all relevant Australian Federal Government and State Government policies and standards (including QGEA and Information Privacy Act).
Establish scalable AI monitoring and reporting that support both foundational controls (model use, cost, benefit) and advanced oversight (model monitoring, drift and performance and incident reporting).
Support the establishment of an AI Governance committee to guide the use of AI within the organisation.
Translate governance requirements into practical playbooks, processes, templates and guidance for teams, including running targeted coaching or education sessions.
Conduct supplier-due diligence for AI capabilities including how data is handled within tools or applications, security attestations and model governance.
What you’ll bring to the role:

Demonstrated experience establishing and/or operating AI governance in complex organisations, including risk and ethics integration, assurance, and audit readiness.
Expert knowledge of public sector frameworks and standards applicable to AI (e.g., QGEA/IS18, Information Privacy Act 2009 (Qld), Privacy Act 1988 (Cth), AI Ethics principles; ISO 42001/23894/38507).
Governance leadership: committee chairing, decision facilitation, stakeholder management, and effective communication of technical risk into business relevant insights
HOW TO APPLY:

Please submit your resume for consideration via the appropriate link. A cover letter demonstrating your relevant experience may also be reviewed.

Job Title: Senior Test Analyst (ETL Test Analyst / Data Platform Test Analyst)
Ad Text:
About Us

Senior Test Analyst (ETL Test Analyst / Data Platform Test Analyst) 
12m FTC + Extension likely
Sydney - Hybrid working (Barangaroo 3dpw)
ASAP start

Let’s create a more sociable future together!

Endeavour Group is Australia’s largest retail drinks network under the Dan Murphy’s and BWS brands. We also run the country's largest portfolio of licensed hotels.

Endeavour Group demerged from Woolworths in 2021 and as part of the transition is taking the opportunity to transform how we operate as an independent business and establish supporting technology.

About the Role

Be uniquely you, come as you are. 
Bring your passion and feel the energy. 

The Senior Test Analyst will be responsible responsible for validating the integrated Endeavour Data Platform (EDP) built on Google Cloud Platform (GCP). Reporting to the Test Lead/Test Manager, you will become an expert in the systems and test processes, providing regular feedback on software quality, defects and execution status. This role involves analyzing complex data flows from source ingestion to business consumption, ensuring data accuracy across all layers. This position will be part of the Data Program.

You will be empowered to challenge project teams to ensure high software quality and provide technical support during User Acceptance Testing (UAT), raising testing risks or those that affect testing timelines or outcomes.

As a key member of the Enterprise Testing team, you will also contribute to the future state testing capability, providing valuable input to continuous improvement initiatives such as test automation, continuous testing, quality metrics and Agile testing.

Sound good? Read on.

Here is a taster of what you can expect in this role:

Requirements Validation: Analyze Business Requirement Documents (BRDs) and High-Level Designs (HLDs) to ensure requirements are buildable and testable for end-to-end data flows.

Test Design & Execution: Design and execute comprehensive test scenarios tracing data from sources (WDP, SAP) through BigQuery layers to consumption points like Tableau.

GCP Technical Testing: Perform extensive validation of BigQuery (partitioning/clustering), Cloud Storage, and Cloud Composer (Airflow) DAG orchestration.

Integration Testing: Validate inbound/outbound interfaces, including Woolworths Data Platform (WDP) 1:1 views, SAP systems (ECC, CAR, PMR), and third-party providers.

Defect Management: Identify, log, and track defects in JIRA, providing detailed evidence and collaborating with engineering teams to triage and resolve issues.

UAT Support: Provide technical assistance to business users, helping investigate issues to determine if they are genuine defects or data gaps.

Vendor & Stakeholder Management: Work closely with external testing vendors, maintain strong relationships with stakeholders in engineering/technology, operations, and business.

Shift Left Testing: Observe and suggest opportunities for seeking feedback on software quality as early as possible in the software development lifecycle (SDLC) for faster feedback and early defect detection.

Continuous Improvement: Champion continuous improvement in testing practices by evaluating emerging tools, processes and technologies, assessing their feasibility, and incorporating them into the testing ecosystem.

Reporting & Metrics: Define and track relevant metrics for test delivery, reporting progress to stakeholders and using insights to refine strategies and improve test coverage and execution efficiency.

What do we need from you

Now let’s talk about you:

Essential Experience and Skills

GCP Data Testing : Experience test planning and executing with strong experience testing data warehouses and platforms specifically within a GCP environment.

Advanced SQL: Proficiency in writing complex SQL queries for data validation, specifically for BigQuery.

Data Modeling: Understanding of dimensional modeling and ETL/ELT transformation processes.

Integration: Experience in understanding integration specification, designing integration tests and executing integration test cases.

Methodologies: Strong background in Agile, DevOps practices, and experience with Shift Left and Shift Right testing.

Experience: Collaborating with development/engineering teams to seek early feedback on software.

Desirable

Emerging Technologies: Familiarity with new trends and technologies in the testing domain, including artificial intelligence (AI), machine learning (ML), and test-driven development (TDD).

Real-time Ingestion: Experience testing Pub/Sub and Dataflow for real-time or near-real-time data processing.

More Information is available on request. 

What's in it for you?

The benefits are good too! 

We offer flexible working in every sense
An exclusive discount card for BWS, Dan Murphy’s, Woolworths, BIG W and other Endeavour Group brands, including our ALH pubs


Monthly meeting-free days 

Your health and wellbeing is your most important asset, and as one of our valued team members, it’s our first priority. You will have a range of free services to help you live well and support your physical, mental and financial wellbeing

Endeavour Group is full of opportunities - use our dedicated learning and development options to grow an idea, yourself, and your career. This is just the start, so dream big.
At Endeavour, we value being a workplace where everyone’s welcome - if you meet a number of the requirements (and not all), we encourage you to apply.
_______________________________
Additional Info:

We are together creators

With a portfolio that includes Dan Murphy’s, BWS, ALH Hotels, Pinnacle Drinks and more, Endeavour Group is big on sociability. Together we create the moments that bring millions of people together. And together we have more fun, create more opportunities, and score a lot more goals. We’re serious about creating a safe, inclusive and fun place to rock up to where equal opportunity is key, and flexibility is part of how we roll.  

We’re all about creating a more sociable future - for our customers and each other. If this job excites you - and you’re close-enough on the requirements, reach out, we’d love to hear from you.

You can learn more about working with us on LinkedIn or at endeavourgroupcareers.com.au.

Our Talent Team and Hiring Leaders kindly request no unsolicited resumes or approaches from Recruitment Agencies. Endeavour Group is not responsible for any fees related to unsolicited resumes.

This role offers meaningful work, career development, and the opportunity to influence policy and strategy across the NSW Government. This role is focused on strategy, policy and project delivery to support the NSW Critical Minerals and High-Tech Metals Strategy 2024-35.

In this role, you will:

Provide high-level advice on policy, regulatory reform, industry trends and emerging issues.
Build and maintain strong stakeholder relationships across government and industry.
Work collaboratively across the Department to develop strategies for the NSW mining and exploration sector.
Lead research and analysis to develop evidence-based options and insights.
Translate complex information into clear, accessible advice for diverse audiences.
Manage discrete projects, including documentation, contracts, reporting and briefings.
Prepare timely, high-quality briefing materials to support senior executive and Ministerial decision making.

This is a great opportunity for someone who enjoys tackling complex problems, driving strategic thinking, and contributing to the long-term direction of the NSW resources industry.

To be successful you’ll be:

Proactive and motivated: A self-starter who can take initiative, think ahead and able to contribute to, lead or manage projects.  
Strong communicator: Exceptional written and verbal communication skills, capable of translating complex information into plain English for executive and Ministerial audiences.
Flexible and adaptable: Open to pivot and change as needed, comfortable with ambiguity, and keen to explore new ideas and solutions.
Curious: An understanding of the broader strategic context we operate in, a keen interest in keeping across global and national developments, and able to consider its impact for NSW.
Familiar with Government processes: Understanding of regulations, legislation, policy and Cabinet processes is a plus.

Why Join Us?

Enjoy opportunities for professional development and career advancement in a dynamic and supportive environment that values strategic thinking and collaboration.
Work closely with various stakeholders across all levels of government and industry.
Support regional communities, enhancing their livelihoods and contributing to the state’s overall prosperity.
Work on meaningful projects that define the role of the NSW resource industry in the global economy.

Things to know about the role:

Compliance with pre-employment probity screening is mandatory and a condition of engagement.

About Us: Together, we are DPIRD

The New South Wales Department of Primary Industries and Regional Development (DPIRD) protects, supports and develops primary industries and regional economies.

Collectively we support strong and sustainable agriculture, forestry, fishing and mining industries, and regional economies. We actively manage our natural assets: our lands and soils, minerals, waterways and oceans, vegetation and forests.

The department brings together:

Local Land Services
NSW Resources
Agriculture and Biosecurity
Fisheries and Forestry
Regional Development and Delivery.

With nearly 5,000 employees, and 75 per cent of the DPIRD team living and working in regional NSW, we are embedded in the regions we serve.

Diversity and inclusion are core DPIRD values. Everyone has the right to contribute and participate to their full potential. We are committed to supporting a diverse and inclusive culture that is respectful, welcoming and flexible – a workplace where our people feel supported, valued, and part of our collective success.

Brunel has partnered with a leading resources company on a contract opportunity for an Data Analyst. Ideal for a data analyst/data scientist with mining and telemetry experience who can turn complex operational data into trusted, actionable insights.

Description

This role delivers data models, analytics, and decision-support tools that improve safety, performance, and operational efficiency of a Collision Avoidance System across mining operations. You'll work across operational, sensor, and spatial datasets to support incident review, optimisation, and strategic decision making, partnering with operations, engineering, and technology teams to define metrics and embed data-driven practices.

Key outcomes:

Analytical models and data pipelines that are robust, accurate, maintainable, and trusted by stakeholders.
Predictive models and statistical analysis using spatial data for creating visualisations, reports and decision making.
Integrated, well-governed datasets combining sensor, geological, and operational data to support repeatable analysis and decision making.
Well-documented business cases and analytical findings that inform product, process, and technology decisions.

Key Responsibilities:

Apply statistical and machine learning techniques to analyse operational and sensor datasets; build predictive models to identify trends and anomalies.
Integrate diverse data sources (sensor, geological, operational) into reliable datasets for analysis and reporting.
Design algorithms that support optimisation and automation, working with developers on proof-of-concepts where needed.
Build dashboards and visualisations that make complex analysis easy to understand, partnering with UI/UX teams as required.
Run stakeholder workshops to gather requirements, identify opportunities, and support adoption of process improvements.
Work with architecture and delivery teams to map analytics impacts to solution requirements.
Partner with IT/data platform teams to ensure data security, integrity, and availability.
Drive continuous improvement by identifying where data can improve safety, productivity, and decision making.

Profile

Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Statistics, or a related discipline.
Proven experience delivering data analytics/data science in an industrial environment, ideally mining.
Strong programming capability in Python (or Matlab/R).
Experience with geospatial tooling (e.g. ArcGIS or similar).
Experience with modern data platforms (Snowflake and AWS analytics services).
Experience with dashboards/visualisation tools (Power BI, Tableau, Grafana or similar).
Strong communication skills and a structured, detail-focused approach to data quality and documentation.
3+ years' experience in mining operations; knowledge of open pit mining (iron ore preferred).

Highly regarded:

Experience with telemetry and sensor datasets (V2X, heavy mobile equipment, or safety systems).
Familiarity with OT environments, mine control, or autonomy operations.
Experience working with large-scale IoT datasets and networks.
Background supporting safety analysis, incident investigations, or continuous improvement programs with data.
Exposure to production-grade data pipelines and cloud analytics tooling.

Ad Text:
RESERVE BANK OF AUSTRALIA - BANKING DEPARTMENT (RBA BK)

Our business is unique in providing financial services to Commonwealth agencies and overseas central banks. The bank plays an important role in the Australian Payment Board, modernising the Australian Payment Industry. There have been increasing number changes recently, especially with the Australian Payment Network announcing the decommission of the Bulk Electronic Clearing System (BECS). This prompts the opportunity to move to other modern payment system such as New Payment Platform (NPP). RBA BK is a major participant in BECS, sending and receiving welfare, pension, Medicare, child support, tax payments etc.

Role Overview:

We are seeking 2 highly skilled and experienced Senior Business Analysts (x1 Perm role & x1 2-year max-term contract) with deep knowledge of payment processing and ISO 20022 messages. In this pivotal role, you will help lead the analysis and implementation of a crucial Australia's payment system. You will be performing impactful work that helps make a difference to the Australian people.

Key Responsibilities:

Prepare and lead Release Planning activities.

Manage and prioritise backlog with support of Product Owner

Prepare and lead agile ceremonies such as Back log refinement, Sprint Prioritisation and Sprint Planning

Elicit, analyse, and document business requirements.

Participate in solution workshops to ensure quality and fitness for purpose.

Propose/Recommend solutions.

Translate and communicate business, strategic, and technical information to a wide range of stakeholders.

Collaborate with internal and external stakeholders.

Collaborate, be a team player.

Help the team continuously improve to deliver high-quality solutions efficiently.

Provide subject matter expert guidance to assist in other delivery aspects such as implementation planning, change management, test planning and training materials.

Help identify and mitigate risks associated with deliverables.

Help build a high-performance team through knowledge sharing.

Provide guidance to senior Business Analyst.


Qualifications and Experience:

Proven experience as a Business Analyst, preferably within the banking or financial services industry.

Proven experience as a Lead Business Analyst, working with various level experienced Business Analysts

Good knowledge and experience of ISO 20022 standards and their application in financial messaging processes.

Exceptional communication and stakeholder management abilities.

Strong understanding of Agile methodologies and experience working within a scrum team.

Excellent critical thinking and problem-solving skills

Experience with NPP and/or BECS is a plus.


Your Team

We're high-performance team in a fast and dynamic environment.

You will be a member of a delivery team consisting of product owner/delivery manager, scrum master, other Business Analysts, testers and developers in agile development.

You will be reporting to the delivery manager.

You will be working collaboratively within your scrum team and across other scrum teams.

You will be encouraged to speak up and use intelligent inquiry in your everyday work, deliverables, and ways of working.

You will be based at Head Office in Sydney.

We're flexible and operate in hybrid model.

Continuous improvement is our DNA so there will be opportunities for learning and growth.



The Reserve Bank of Australia is committed to equity, diversity and inclusion through key initiatives. We welcome and encourage applicants from diverse backgrounds to apply, including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples, culturally and linguistically diverse background, those living with a disability and from the LGBTQ+ community. What's the role?

We’re looking for a Research Director to help us reinvent how research and insight is done at News Corp Australia. Reporting to the Head of Research, you won't be a traditional Director; rather, you will be someone obsessed with the future of research, technology, and generative AI, finding ways to make insight work faster, smarter, and more impactful. You will be passionate about turning audience insight into decisions that improve products and commercial outcomes, while working on projects that influence the future direction of the country and advocate for a better Australia.

In this role, you will:

Lead Strategic Research: Craft and lead high-impact research programs across diverse topics like media, sport, and the economy. These programs will inform product vision, company priorities, and long-term bets in an AI era.

Modern Execution: Design and conduct quantitative and qualitative research yourself and through external agencies. You'll use modern analytics and AI tools to accelerate analysis while retaining strong human judgement.

Data Synthesis: Triangulate and verify insights by combining multiple data sources primary research, first-party data, and third-party sources to build robust, defensible conclusions.

Commercial Storytelling: Deliver commercially-oriented insights through influential storytelling and strategic foresight to support decision-making across business units.

Team Leadership: Manage a Research Manager and model leadership behaviours that inspire the team, contributing to the development of a best-in-class capability within the Growth Intelligence Centre.

Who are you?

Experience & Background: 8+ years’ experience in market research or insights with an agency background preferred. You are currently functioning as a Research Director or a Senior Manager ready to step up.

Future-Focused Mindset: You aren't a traditional researcher. You are energised by the future of insights and excited to experiment with generative AI tools to automate work and amplify impact.

Technical Expertise: Deep experience designing quantitative or mixed-method studies and conducting market sizing. You have advanced knowledge of Q or SPSS, Excel, and research knowledge platforms.

Analytical Rigour: A demonstrated ability to cross-check and stress-test insights using multiple data sources with high attention to detail and quality standards.

Communication Skills: Excellent presentation and storytelling abilities. You can connect disparate information into clear narratives for senior stakeholders and clients.

Collaborative Drive: A proactive, opportunity-spotting mindset with strong skills in managing stakeholders, cross-functional teams, and supplier relationships.

Exclusively ours - Access to publications and products from across the News Corp family

Time off - News offers a range of leave options to support your personal needs and moments that matter in life: Parental leave, Birthday leave, Volunteer leave, Career break and Compassionate leave.

Helping you grow - Development opportunities (including diversity and inclusion - focused education series) and recognition

Giving back - Make a difference to our communities.

We are Australia’s number one and most influential media organisation with more than 150 prestige brands across news, sport and lifestyle. Each month more than 17 million Australians choose to consume news and information from our digital and print products – more than any other media group in Australia.

About us

We create thriving places and connected communities. We bring together transport, planning, land use, precinct and policy functions in a single department to deliver the best outcomes for Victorians.

Together with our portfolio agencies, we are responsible for planning, building, operating and +maintaining Victoria's transport, planning and land services for use by all.

The Resource and Capability Manager is a key leadership role within the Data & Digital division, responsible for managing a team of project managers and business analysts within the Delivery Branch. This role leads a team of skilled professionals responsible for the successful delivery of Data & Digital projects, meeting organisational objectives and tailored to evolving stakeholder needs.

Key Selection Criteria

The key selection criteria emphasise strong leadership in people management, project delivery and workforce capability development. The role requires the ability to translate organisational strategies into programs and workforce plans, drive performance, champion continuous improvement, and build a culture that enables others to excel. Advanced business analysis skills are also essential, with the capability to apply analytical frameworks in complex settings and contribute to organisational capability uplift.

To access the Position Description, Please click here

Position accountabilities

DTP is seeking an experienced leader to uplift project delivery capability across its Data & Digital division. This role provides assurance and oversight of project and business analysis practices, ensuring compliance with standards, methodologies, and governance requirements. A key focus will be fostering a high-performance culture that promotes collaboration, continuous improvement, and rigorous project disciplines to support successful delivery outcomes.

The position will lead resource planning and optimisation activities, aligning workforce capabilities with project objectives, timelines, and budgets. This includes developing fit-for-purpose resource plans, capacity planning, and development pathways that enhance team performance and adaptability. The role will also champion continuous improvement across project practices and support change initiatives that uplift systems, processes, and portfolio outcomes.Success requires strong analytical and strategic thinking skills, the ability to identify improvement opportunities, and the capacity to influence stakeholders across technical and executive domains. Applicants will bring expertise in risk management, professional development, and cross-functional collaboration, with the confidence to ensure issues are proactively identified and addressed. • Experience relevant to the accountabilities and capabilities of the role. (mandatory)

• Formal qualifications in Business and /or Systems Analysis (e.g. CCBA). (desirable)

As an equal opportunity employer, we are committed to fostering a safe, inclusive, and high-performance culture. Through shared actions and behaviours aligned with our strategy and direction, we empower our people to thrive and meaningfully contribute to the department's goals.

Data Governance Advisor

6 Month Contract | $1,200 - $1,350 + Super / Day | Sydney (Hybrid)

We are partnering with a leading Australian university undertaking a significant enterprise Data Governance uplift aligned to a broader digital and data transformation program.

This is a hands-on, embedded role working directly with the Enterprise Data Governance Lead to operationalise governance across priority domains including Student and HR data.

This is not a policy writing or purely advisory engagement. We are seeking a practitioner who has implemented governance in complex, federated organisations and can operate confidently between strategy and execution.

The Opportunity

You will play a key role in translating enterprise data governance intent into practical, adoptable standards and artefacts that can be embedded into delivery and business-as-usual rhythms.

Key focus areas include:

Designing and operationalising minimum viable governance standards.
Defining stewardship models, decision-rights and accountability structures.
Establishing data classification, sensitivity and usage controls.
Contributing to AI and advanced analytics governance requirements.
Supporting governance forums and assurance mechanisms.
Developing practical templates, artefacts and “how-to” guidance.
Facilitating workshops and enabling adoption across faculties and portfolios.
Mentoring internal team members to build sustainable governance capability.
You will work closely with data platform, reporting and domain delivery teams to ensure governance is integrated, not bolted on.

About You

You are a proven Data Governance practitioner who has:

Implemented (not just designed) enterprise data governance frameworks.
Produced governance artefacts that were adopted in practice.
Worked in complex, federated environments (higher education or public sector highly regarded).
Balanced rigour with pragmatism and organisational readiness.
Operated comfortably across senior stakeholders.
Strong influencing, facilitation and mentoring capability.
Experience supporting AI governance or enterprise data platform programs will be highly regarded.

What’s on Offer

6 month contract with strong likelihood of extension
$1,200 - $1,350 + super / day (depending on experience)
Hybrid working - 3 days onsite in Sydney, 2 days WFH
High-impact role within a major institutional transformation
This is an opportunity to contribute meaningfully to an enterprise-wide uplift that will underpin analytics, regulatory obligations and future AI capability at scale.

If you’re a hands-on governance leader who thrives in complex environments and enjoys building capability as you deliver, we’d welcome a confidential discussion.

Job description:



DISCOVER A BRIGHTER FUTURE

At South32, we're meeting the challenge of enabling a sustainable future through our focus on responsibly producing commodities critical for a low-carbon world. As a collaborative, caring and inclusive company, there's no better place to make a genuine difference. Together we're making a positive, global impact that has the potential to change lives. Whatever career path you choose, we'll support you every step of the way to learn, grow and succeed. So join us, step towards a brighter future and leave your legacy.


ABOUT WORSLEY

Are you looking to be home every night? If so, this is your opportunity to live, work and play a short drive from stunning coastlines, scenic trails, magnificent jarrah forests and the food and wine heartland of the South-West and Peel Regions of Western Australia.

Our integrated Bauxite Mine, Alumina Refinery and Port Operation is creating the essential products needed for a sustainable low carbon future and is on a journey to become the world's leading Alumina producer where our workforce value the lifestyle that Worsley Alumina has to offer.

WHAT SOUTH32 OFFERS

26 weeks full-paid, or 52 weeks half-paid parental leave for primary carers.
Annual short-term incentive bonus that recognises both your individual performance and the overall success of the business.
Discounted rates on travel, healthcare, and technology products.

Ability to purchase up to 4 weeks of additional annual leave.

ABOUT THE ROLE

This is a Permanent, Monday to Friday, 40-hour per week roster. This role will be based at our Worsley Alumina Refinery which is a short drive from Collie (15 minutes), Bunbury (35 minutes) and other nearby scenic communities.

As there is no accommodation on site, you will be required to drive in, drive out on a daily basis. Employees ideally live within an hour's drive of Collie.

As the Analyst Finance Business Partnership, you will be responsible for providing expert financial analysis and advice to support operations in achieving optimal business outcomes.

Key responsibilities include, but are not limited to:

Partnering with operational leaders during budgeting and monthly forecasting cycles
Interpreting cost drivers and clearly explaining impacts on performance and outcomes
Supporting contract set‑up and variations with clear financial input
Strengthening site adherence to financial governance, standards and procedures
Working closely with operational teams to resolve finance‑related issues
Contributing to continuous improvement through data‑led insights and practical recommendations

ABOUT YOU

You will have experience and demonstrate capability in the following:

Working in a finance business partnering or management reporting environment
Building effective, trusted relationships with operational and senior stakeholders
Translating complex information into clear, practical insights for non‑finance audiences
Managing multiple priorities with confidence, curiosity and a collaborative approach
Proficiency in finance software, including SAP & Excel (Power BI advantageous)

Qualifications for this position are:

CA/CPA with relevant Finance Experience

Relocation may be considered for the successful candidate.

South32 is committed to building and maintaining an inclusive and diverse workforce that reflects the communities in which we operate. We provide a recruitment process that is fair, equitable and accessible for all and we encourage candidates from all backgrounds to apply.

The job advert will close on Friday 27 February 2026

Company Description


It all started in sunny San Diego, California in 2004 when a visionary engineer, Fred Luddy, saw the potential to transform how we work. Fast forward to today — ServiceNow stands as a global market leader, bringing innovative AI-enhanced technology to over 8,100 customers, including 85% of the Fortune 500®. But this is just the beginning of our journey. Join us as we pursue our purpose to make the world work better for everyone.

Job Description


ServiceNow is actively seeking a Senior Strategist for our Inspire Value – Australia & NZ team. As a crucial pillar within ServiceNow’s global industry and solutions organisation, the Inspire Value team are senior, customer-facing strategic advisors who partner directly with C-suite and Board-level executives to shape which business problems are worth solving, where to invest, and how to unlock measurable value through digital, business and AI transformation.

Operating at the intersection of business strategy, financial rigor, and enterprise technology, this role supports high-impact customer conversations, reframing technology discussions into strategic decisions around growth, resilience, productivity, and risk, and aligning stakeholders around a shared investment narrative.

Leveraging ServiceNow’s Now Value methodology, the Strategist architects and leads value-led transformation engagements, translating complex platform capabilities into clear, defensible investment cases that influence executive decision-making and accelerate strategic outcomes. In must-win situations, they act as a trusted, independent advisor, bringing clarity to ambiguity, challenging assumptions, and guiding customers toward confident, outcome-driven decisions.

As a senior partner to Sales leadership, account teams, and customer executives, the Inspire Value Strategist plays a critical role in orchestrating value across our most strategic customer accounts, ensuring consistency of message, alignment of priorities, and sustained executive confidence throughout the transformation journey.

What you get to do in this role:

This role combines strategic leadership with customer impact and team building in three core areas:

1. Strategic growth and executive influence

Engage with customer executives to help shape their most critical business challenges and transformation decisions
Partner with Sales Leaders to define and execute the regional strategic deals and growth strategy
Create compelling, board-level investment cases (including TCO, ROI, and risk analysis) for value-led transformations that routinely close multi-million-dollar strategic deals
Support executive vision and value workshops with C-suite and Board-level, representing ServiceNow as a strategic thought partner for value-led strategic business transformations
Help shape the future of our customers by identifying critical market trends and emerging needs that could lead to partnerships to accelerate our customers growth and impact in their business

2. Be a trusted strategic advisor

Serve as a strategic advisor on must-win deals, crafting and delivering bespoke value propositions and business cases to C-level decision-makers.
Instill a culture of analytical rigor by through high-impact customer propositions and engagements
Drive adoption of best practices in strategic value-selling across the region, including detailed value analysis, benchmarking, and executive messaging

3. Organizational alignment and innovation

Foster a community of collaboration and knowledge sharing, working across internal functions to ensure consistent messaging and direction
Create thought leadership, including industry points of views, best practices, white papers, and executive workshops, establishing NOW as the platform for business transformation
Act as a market and industry expert, providing data-driven feedback and expertise to Engineering, Product and Solutions to drive continuous product and service improvement

Qualifications


We seek candidates who thrive on complex problem-solving and possess:

Experience in strategy consulting, value advisory, or related roles, with a strong foundation in analytical problem-solving and structured thinking
Demonstrated experience supporting complex, cross-functional initiatives and contributing to high-impact customer or executive engagements
Strong communication skills with the ability to present insights clearly and credibly to senior stakeholders
A proactive mindset with the ability to take ownership of workstreams, deliver high-quality outputs, and continuously build expertise

To be successful in this role you have:

Experience in leveraging or critically thinking about how to integrate AI into work processes, decision-making, or problem-solving. This may include using AI-powered tools, automating workflows, analyzing AI-driven insights, or exploring AI's potential impact on the function or industry.
Experience: 10+ years of experience in strategy consulting, value advisory, corporate strategy, or similar roles
 Strategic acumen: Analytical and financial experience with the ability to build compelling business and investment cases and quantify complex strategic value
Strategic consulting toolkit: Exceptional skills to build relationships and influencing outcomes, coupled with the integrity, empathy and passion for our mission and customer success
Adaptability: Ability to balance complex requirements, drive agreement across stakeholders, and quickly learn new solutions, functional, or industry domains
Technology fluency: Experience with enterprise cloud solutions (NOW platform experience is a significant advantage)
 Industry expertise: Deep industry domain expertise in one or more industries, preferable in Financial Services, Government, Telecommunications, Technology, Natural Resources and Energy
 Flexibility: Ability to travel up to 50% of the time across Australia & New Zealand

We are seeking a Contract Senior Data Architect / Data Modeller to lead the design of a common enterprise data model supporting the migration of fragmented data assets from SAS NEO to a Databricks Lakehouse platform.

This role plays a critical part in establishing a unified, governed data foundation that standardises core entities, definitions, and relationships across the organisation, enabling scalable analytics, reporting, and AI/ML use cases.

You will work across architecture, data engineering, analytics, and business teams to rationalise existing schemas, translate embedded business logic, and define canonical domains aligned to modern Lakehouse and cloud data architecture principles.

Key Responsibilities
Design conceptual, logical, and physical data models supporting enterprise analytics and AI
Define canonical data domains, entities, and relationships
Map legacy SAS NEO datasets and unstructured sources to target Databricks models
Translate embedded business logic into governed, reusable data structures
Define OLTP, OLAP, and dimensional models (star/snowflake)
Establish metadata, lineage, and documentation standards
Ensure alignment with Lakehouse, ELT, and cloud architecture patterns
Collaborate with engineers, architects, and stakeholders on target-state design
Required Skills & Experience
Strong experience in Data Architecture, Data Modelling & Design
Proven migration experience to Databricks or Lakehouse platforms
Conceptual, logical and physical modelling expertise
Dimensional modelling (star/snowflake) and OLTP vs OLAP design
Advanced SQL
Experience with relational databases (SQL Server, Oracle, Postgres, MySQL, SAS)
Cloud platforms: Azure, AWS or GCP
Data integration & ETL/ELT design patterns
Metadata management, lineage, and governance frameworks
Nice to Have
Python, Scala, or Spark
Informatica, ADF, Talend, Boomi, SSIS
Kafka / Event Hubs / streaming
Power BI, Tableau, Qlik
MDM and data quality tooling
Infrastructure-as-code exposure (Terraform / ARM)
If you would like to hear more please APPLY below. Australian Citizens or PR only.

We’re looking for a highly analytical, data-driven marketer who gets excited by digging into raw data, uncovering patterns, and turning insight into action. Someone who thrives on understanding customer journeys end-to-end and using data to fuel smarter lead generation, automation and campaign performance.

 

About the role



As the Marketing Insights & Lead Generation Manager, you will play a critical role in building and scaling an elite, data-led lead generation engine for Vocus.




This role is about deep analysis, insight generation and optimisation. You will work hand-in-glove with our Marketing Automation & CRM Manager, using data to inform how leads are sourced, segmented, nurtured, scored and converted across the funnel.




You’ll be responsible for analysing various data sets (CRM, campaign, behavioural, customer and third-party data), identifying opportunities, and translating insight into clear actions that improve demand generation, campaign effectiveness and customer experience.

 

What you’ll be responsible for



Lead Generation & Demand Optimisation

Analyse lead, opportunity and campaign data to identify performance drivers, gaps and optimisation opportunities across the full funnel
Support the design and ongoing refinement of lead nurture programs, working closely with the Marketing Automation & CRM Manager
Use insights to inform targeting, segmentation, messaging, CTAs and offers to improve conversion and pipeline contribution

 

Customer & Market Insights

Deeply analyse customer behaviour, preferences and buying signals across Simple Enterprise, Mid-Market and SMB segments
Identify trends, patterns and opportunities from raw data sets and translate them into actionable insights
Analyse competitive offers and market activity to inform positioning, propositions and campaign strategy

 

Customer Journey Analysis

Map and continuously refine customer journeys using data to understand drop-off points, friction and moments of opportunity
Cross-match behavioural, campaign and CRM data to uncover how customers move through the funnel and lifecycle
Identify opportunities for personalisation, automation and smarter engagement at each stage

 

Data Analysis & Reporting

Own the analysis and interpretation of marketing and sales data, turning complex data into clear, compelling insights
Build and maintain dashboards, reports and ad-hoc analysis to support decision-making (monthly MBRs and on-demand reporting)
Track and report on key KPIs including lead quality, conversion rates, pipeline contribution, campaign ROI and customer engagement

 

CRM & Data Management (Salesforce)

Support end-to-end lead and data management within Salesforce, including data enrichment, list processing and lead reporting
Partner closely with CRM, SFMC and data teams to ensure data integrity, usability and insight generation
Support opportunity campaign creation for outbound sales and coordination of EDM and communication lists

 

Collaboration & Stakeholder Engagement

Work closely with the Marketing Automation & CRM Manager to operationalise insights into automated journeys and campaigns
Partner with sales, digital performance, segment leads and data teams to align insight, execution and outcomes
Communicate insights clearly to stakeholders, helping teams understand the “so what” and “what next”

 

What you’ll bring to the role



Experience & Background

8–10+ years’ experience in B2B marketing, insights, demand generation or analytics-focused roles
Experience in telecommunications, technology, SaaS or digital infrastructure highly regarded
Degree in Marketing, Business, Analytics, Data, or equivalent industry experience (MBA or analytics qualifications highly regarded)

 

Capabilities & Skills

Strong data and analytical capability - confident working with large, complex data sets
Advanced Excel skills (pivot tables, formulas, data manipulation) and strong reporting capability
Experience working with CRM and marketing automation platforms (Salesforce / SFMC experience highly regarded)
Deep understanding of lead generation mechanics, funnels, lifecycle marketing and customer journeys
Commercially minded with the ability to translate data into clear, actionable recommendations
Comfortable operating in fast-paced, evolving environments with ambiguity

Mirvac has created some of Australia's most iconic places, from thriving residential communities, to landmark offices and mixed-use precincts. At the heart of every project: a deep commitment to our customers, and an ambition to reimagine urban life.

Our opportunity

We have an opportunity for a Senior Research Analyst (depending on experience, Research Analyst is a possibility), you will provide high quality insights of market performance, risks and return drivers for the Group and external clients. Craft analytics & insights spanning economic, demographic, capital market and property spheres for a variety of internal and external clients.

Your responsibilities will include:


Play an integral role in the Group Research team while liaising with business stakeholders from various divisions including Investments, Funds Management, Asset Management, Development, Investor Relations, and Corporate Services on requirements

The Senior Manager, Statistical Programming is responsible for planning and executing or overseeing projects by coordinating staff and processes to deliver projects on time, within budget and with the desired outcomes while ensuring the trial is conducted in accordance with the protocol, company Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs), ICH GCP guidelines and other applicable regulatory requirements.

Core Responsibilities
• Provide technical leadership and oversight for statistical programming deliverables, ensuring high-quality, compliant datasets, tables, listings, and figures through effective cross-functional collaboration and adherence to CDISC standards, regulatory requirements, and internal SOPs.
• Analyse study protocols, statistical analysis plans, and sponsor requirements to translate business and research needs into technical programming specifications.
• Develop, modify, and validate SAS programs to generate clinical datasets, tables, listings, and figures (TLFs) in accordance with CDISC SDTM and ADaM standards.
• Perform unit testing, debugging, validation, and documentation of statistical programs to ensure data integrity and reproducibility.
• Maintain and enhance existing programming codebases, implementing improvements to efficiency, reliability, and standardisation.
• Collaborate with Biostatistics, Data Management, PK, Clinical Operations, and Medical Writing teams to ensure technical consistency, accurate data flow, and timely delivery of programming outputs.
• Identify, analyse, and resolve programming defects, performance issues, and data inconsistencies throughout the project lifecycle.
• Ensure all programming activities comply with internal SOPs, regulatory requirements, and applicable quality standards.
• Contribute to the development, maintenance, and optimisation of programming macros, utilities, libraries, and tools to support scalable and reusable solutions.
• Participate in peer code reviews and quality checks to ensure adherence to technical standards and best practices.
• Support audit and inspection activities by providing technical explanations, programming documentation, and validated outputs as required.
• Provide technical guidance and knowledge sharing to colleagues on programming methodologies, standards, and tools, as needed.
• Perform other programming-related duties as directed by the Line Manager.


Departmental Responsibilities
• Collaborate effectively with members of the Biometrics department to support integrated technical delivery of clinical data outputs.
• Identify and mitigate technical risks related to statistical programming deliverables.
• Participate in technical training and continuous professional development related to programming tools, standards, and methodologies.
• Contribute to continuous improvement initiatives relating to programming processes, standards, and automation.
• Manage sponsor communication, project timelines, risks, and programming-related resources, including forecasting, change control, and issue resolution, to ensure successful and timely project delivery.


Qualifications, Skills and Experience
• Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, Software Engineering, or a related quantitative discipline.
• Minimum 5 years of hands-on programming experience, with the majority of time spent writing, testing, and maintaining code.
• Demonstrated expertise in SAS programming, including development of SDTM and ADaM datasets.
• Strong experience in application-style programming logic, data processing workflows, and system optimisation.
• Proven ability to analyse requirements and translate them into technical solutions.
• Experience working within regulated environments and adhering to documented standards and procedures.
• Strong problem-solving, debugging, and analytical skills.

What we offer

Stimulating work
Project diversity
An intellectual challenge
An agile & flexible workplace
Opportunity to progress
Stability
Sense of community
A leadership team that are working together on a common goal
Flexible work options
Great tools / tech to do your job
A competitive salary & an extra days holiday for your birthday!

Principal Data Architect

Contract for 12 months| Brisbane CBD | Hybrid working

Brisbane based candidates only

We are partnering with a leading Queensland Government client to recruit an experienced Principal Data Architect. In this role, you will lead the design and implementation of the department’s central data capability – a strategic function that unifies data architecture, governance, engineering and business intelligence analysis into a coordinated service model.

Key Requirements:

Work with business stakeholders to understand and map key business capabilities and processes, ensuring data architecture reflects business functions and supports strategic outcomes.

Review existing systems and data flows to define current-state architecture. Design and maintain enterprise data architecture aligned with DSDIP’s ICT strategy and government standards.

Monitor data needs across divisions, guiding projects to avoid duplication and promoting shared solutions.

Engage with business stakeholders on data needs and develop high-level requirements and solution design  that can be used to engage delivery partners. Collaborate with ICT delivery partners and vendors to ensure seamless integration of data solutions and alignment with enterprise architecture.

Review and validate detailed designs to ensure alignment with architecture, security and privacy standards.

What We’re Looking For?

Experience in data architecture or senior data roles in complex organisations.

Strong skills in business and data modelling, integration, and architecture using platforms like Microsoft Azure, Dynamics 365, ArcGIS, SQL, and Power BI

Sound knowledge of governance, metadata, privacy and security frameworks.

Proven leadership and stakeholder engagement skills.

Relevant qualifications or equivalent experience; certifications (e.g., Azure, TOGAF) and knowledge of QLD Government ICT frameworks are desirable.

Job Title: Senior Financial Performance & Analysis Analyst- 6 month contract
Ad Text:
About Us

Join us at Cleanaway and contribute to making a sustainable future possible, together.

We transform waste into resources and renewable energy.  When you start to think of waste as a resource, it opens a world of possibilities.

As a high growth, ASX listed organisation with over 10,000 employees, our goal is to be recognised by our customers as the most innovative and sustainable waste management company with industry leading HSE performance.  We are Australia’s largest company in this sector, providing essential services to millions of customers and communities nationally.

The Opportunity

We are seeking a highly capable and commercially minded Senior FP&A Analyst to join Cleanaway’s Group Finance team on a 6-month fixed-term contract. 

Sitting within the Group FP&A function, this role plays an integral part in delivering Cleanaway’s financial planning and reporting processes, including forecast and monthly reporting. You’ll be responsible for preparing analysis, interpreting financial performance, and providing insights that support decision-making across Group and Corporate stakeholders. Further, you’ll be leading the KPI and Value Driver reporting process, including governance on metrics and reporting. 

This is a hands-on role that would suit an experienced analyst who enjoys the structure of ASX and BAU cycles, has excellent attention to detail, and is confident working with financial systems and large data sets. You will work closely with other analysts, Corporate Finance, and business partners across the Strategic Business Units (SBUs). 

 

Key Responsibilities 

Support the forecasting and budgeting process, working with finance business partners to consolidate, review, and validate inputs. 
Supporting and developing our Key Performance Indicators and Value Drivers across our segments, including the reporting and governance framework.

About the Role/Team

Finance at Canva is on an exciting journey—scaling the foundations that support a rapidly growing global company, while making our processes smarter, simpler, and more empowering for our teams. The Finance Transformation team sits at the heart of this mission.

We're looking for a Finance Transformation Senior Manager who’s passionate about solving complex problems, improving processes end-to-end, and helping teams work more efficiently through technology, automation, and AI-enabled solutions. You’ll work cross-functionally across Finance, along with Finance Systems, Finance Data and the broader business, helping shape and execute Canva’s finance transformation projects — with a focus on process reengineering, driving simplification, automation and AI-driven solutions. You’ll help share the future of how Finance works at Canva.

If you love digging into business processes, running cross-functional projects, driving change, and finding opportunities to streamline and simplify — this role is made for you.

What you’ll do (responsibilities)

Lead Finance Process Transformation: Identify, design, and deliver scalable improvements across key global finance processes (Revenue, Billing, Payables, Reporting, etc.), balancing innovation with strong control and compliance. Help embed AI-enabled ways of working, drive adoption and education, help teams identify problems and expected outcomes - focusing on efficiency, accuracy, repeatability, and standardisation.
Project, Program and Change Management: Lead transformation programs of varying scale, ensuring cross-functional stakeholder alignment, governance, and smooth change adoption across teams. Coordinate project activities, dependencies, and timelines to ensure alignment between teams.Help unblock, remove ambiguity, and support smooth project execution.
Drive Technology Enablement: Partner with Finance Systems, Data, and Engineering teams to implement automation, system integrations, and AI-based solutions that streamline end-to-end workflows.
Help shape the Transformation Roadmap: Collaborating with finance and business leaders to define the strategic direction for the Finance Technology stack and transformation priorities.
Data, Insight & Automation: Champion data-driven decision-making - ensuring finance data is leveraged effectively for reporting, analytics, and automation.

What we're looking for

Significant experience in Finance Transformation, or Process Improvement roles (experience in fast-scaling tech, SaaS, or global environments strongly preferred).
A background in Finance with a Bachelor's degree in Finance, Accounting, Business Administration, or a related field is a big plus.
Experience with driving process redesign. Strong analytical and problem-solving skills, able to break down ambiguity into actionable steps.
Familiarity with finance ERP, billing and reporting systems (e.g., Workday, Netsuite, Zuora, Salesforce, Anaplan) and an understanding of data and automation and AI platforms.
Proven ability to lead large scale transformation programs end-to-end from strategy and design to implementation and embedding.
A balance of big-picture vision and detail orientation, with a strong understanding of finance processes and data flows.
Excellent stakeholder management and communication skills; able to work cross-functionally without effort, translating between finance, technical and business teams.
Growth mindset. Passion for continuous improvement and leveraging new technologies (AI, automation, analytics) to elevate finance impact and scale finance operations.

We'd love it if you have:

Familiarity with Agile, Lean, or continuous improvement approaches.

We’re a small new team that is just getting started, so you aren’t afraid to roll up your sleeves, get into the detail. Able to determine and play whatever role is needed to make projects a success: analyst, project coordinator, facilitator, tester, or change champion.

Why You’ll Love It Here

You’ll shape the future of how finance operates at one of the world’s most loved design platforms.

You’ll work with world-class teams across Finance, IT, Data and the business in an environment that encourages experimentation and learning.

You’ll have autonomy and ownership to lead high-impact transformation initiatives that directly influence Canva’s scalability and success.

What's in it for you?

Achieving our crazy big goals motivates us to work hard - and we do - but you'll experience lots of moments of magic, connectivity and fun woven throughout life at Canva, too. We also offer a range of benefits to set you up for every success in and outside of work.

Flexible leave options that empower you to be a force for good, take time to recharge and supports you personally
